1
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:25,280
Are you from out of town?

2
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,360
I dress exactly like celebrities.

3
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:30,640
How do you know I'm from out of town?

4
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:32,440
You guys are siblings, aren't you?

5
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,600
Come on. Let's go.

6
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:36,920
Petch.

7
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:40,240
Where were you all this time?

8
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:44,800
The judge sent Petch to the Juvenile
Training Center for five years.

9
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:49,640
But with his good behavior,
he got out early.

10
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:52,440
He just got out earlier this month.

11
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:54,600
If you don't succeed,

12
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,280
you won't face anyone,

13
00:03:57,920 --> 00:03:59,560
including me.

14
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:03,080
PREVIOUSLY

15
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:12,720
Fill it up, please.

16
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:22,280
Petch.

17
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:25,480
It's really you.

18
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:29,760
I'm not the Petch that you know, ma'am.

19
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:33,280
What?

20
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,120
Full tank, ma'am?

21
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,640
Do you really not know who I am?

22
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:41,680
I'm just a gas station attendant.

23
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:42,720
I mean, look at me.

24
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:44,840
So?

25
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:47,920
Does a gas station attendant
have no right to know me?

26
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:49,760
Are you crazy?

27
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,760
Yes, I am crazy.

28
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:56,520
I'm way crazier than you think.

29
00:04:58,320 --> 00:04:59,160
Leave me alone.

30
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,480
- Leave.
- Petch.

31
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,880
You can't do this, Petch.

32
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:04,800
Petch!

33
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,760
I don't believe
that you forgot everything.

34
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:10,360
The noodle shop,
the concert we went to together.

35
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:12,400
Did it not mean anything to you?

36
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:18,560
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

37
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:25,120
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

38
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:31,520
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

39
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:36,600
<i>But never reaching you</i>

40
00:05:37,760 --> 00:05:42,440
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

41
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:49,360
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

42
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:55,200
<i>I'm just an ordinary woman</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

43
00:05:55,720 --> 00:06:01,600
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

44
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:07,400
<i>You are out of reach</i>

45
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:13,240
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

46
00:06:23,440 --> 00:06:25,320
I know you remember us.

47
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:31,000
Do you know how devastated I've been
in the past four years?

48
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:40,880
Dao.

49
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,800
I never forgot you.

50
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:47,120
Not even for a day.

51
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:51,320
But…

52
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,200
But?

53
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,640
I realized that

54
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,000
we can't bring those days back.

55
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,360
You haven't even started yet.

56
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:04,360
Are you giving up already?

57
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:06,520
Do you have any idea

58
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:09,760
where I've spent my life
in the past four years?

59
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:13,120
You were sent to juvie for murder.

60
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:17,320
How did you know?

61
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,000
I went to see Mr. Nop.

62
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:23,200
He told me everything
about your stupidity.

63
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,040
Good.

64
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:27,320
I'm stupid.

65
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:29,360
I'm the bad guy,

66
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:30,560
so you don't have to see me again.

67
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:31,880
Wait, Petch.

68
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:37,040
Stop telling me what to do

69
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:39,960
and listen to me.

70
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:45,640
Whether you're rich or poor,

71
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:47,800
whether your record is clean or not,

72
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:50,280
you're still Petch.

73
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:53,760
My feelings for you stay the same.

74
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:05,320
Petch! Let's have lunch!

75
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:08,200
Dao?

76
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,080
How did you get here?

77
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:16,280
How many times do I have to tell you?

78
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:19,680
This is not the place to be lazy
or you'll be fired.

79
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:21,840
No need to fire me.

80
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:23,240
I quit.

81
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:24,320
Petch.

82
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,160
Let's end it here.

83
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,960
I don't want to see you again.

84
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:35,640
Petch!

85
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:43,000
If you guys can't take a little scolding,
how are you going to get anywhere in life?

86
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,920
I'm sorry, sir.

87
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:50,000
Nobody can stand a boss
who does nothing but shout all day!

88
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:52,840
Dam! Wait for me!

89
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:08,040
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

90
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:14,120
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

91
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:21,040
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

92
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:25,720
<i>But never reaching you</i>

93
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:31,760
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

94
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:38,480
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

95
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:44,880
<i>I'm just an ordinary woman</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

96
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:50,680
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

97
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,440
Oh, wow.

98
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:57,560
This is exquisite.

99
00:09:58,080 --> 00:10:01,040
Did you really buy this for me?

100
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:03,600
Yes. It's for you, Mom.

101
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:07,240
I mean, "ma'am."

102
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:10,800
Are you practicing being my in-law?

103
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:13,280
I would ask for an expensive dowry.

104
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:15,800
I would let you make the call.

105
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:19,240
I'm willing to pay you the dowry.

106
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:27,520
Ms. Dao.

107
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:29,000
Good to see you.

108
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:32,120
I've made your favorite
coconut milk jelly.

109
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,720
- Thank you.
- All right.

110
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:39,000
You made this for whom?

111
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:41,200
For Ake.

112
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:42,920
He's here?

113
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:46,200
Yes. He's in the living room,
talking to your mom.

114
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:49,240
With your permission,
I must bring Ake his dessert now.

115
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:55,480
Where are you heading out, dear?

116
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,440
To the grocery.

117
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:02,160
Save that for later.
Come, have dinner with me. I'm hungry.

118
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:04,160
I'm glad that we can have dinner together.

119
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:11,720
Thanks.

120
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:21,000
Thank you, Ake,
for always being kind to me.

121
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:23,200
But this jewelry

122
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:28,520
isn't as important as the true love
you have for my daughter.

123
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:30,840
Ma'am.

124
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:35,080
I believe you know
that I've been seeing no one but Dao.

125
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:39,000
My heart is screaming
my proposal to her right now.

126
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,560
But…

127
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:43,880
Dao won't say yes for sure.

128
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,440
Of course not.

129
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:48,920
She'll let her parents decide.

130
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:52,400
How about we arrange the engagement now?

131
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,600
I won't get engaged to him.

132
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:57,120
Dao.

133
00:11:57,640 --> 00:11:59,880
There's no way you can make me
get engaged to Ake.

134
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:03,920
Dao, take it easy.

135
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,280
Dao.

136
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:09,840
I've sacrificed everything
for your happiness.

137
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:11,600
Happiness?

138
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:14,560
I know the word but…

139
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:16,560
You know what?

140
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:18,960
I never feel it.

141
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:22,480
Can you and Dad
stop making decisions for me?

142
00:12:22,560 --> 00:12:24,160
I can't take this anymore.

143
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:26,360
- Dao!
- Sweetheart.

144
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:29,320
Don't do this.

145
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:33,200
Let go of me. Let me live my life.

146
00:12:34,640 --> 00:12:35,880
Dao!

147
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,960
Pen.

148
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:43,440
- Ma'am?
- Pen!

149
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:45,320
Ma'am.

150
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:46,440
Mom!

151
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:49,640
Sir, we should take her to the hospital.

152
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:51,360
- Okay.
- Excuse me, ma'am.

153
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:06,920
Enough of this nonsense.
If you two won't talk, I will.

154
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:08,880
What?

155
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:11,240
Who's that girl?

156
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:13,920
Why did you have to quit your job
when she came?

157
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:16,480
Sai, finish your meal.

158
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,920
It's bothering me.

159
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,640
I feel that there's something going on.

160
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:25,280
That girl…

161
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,960
Is she your girlfriend?

162
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:30,520
Can't you just keep it to yourself?

163
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:32,480
You keep your mouth shut.

164
00:13:32,560 --> 00:13:34,080
Petch, answer me.

165
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:36,600
No, she isn't.

166
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:38,760
I'm done.

167
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:46,120
There's something between them for sure.
I'll get the answer.

168
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,440
Where are you going?

169
00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:50,240
Why do you have to know, huh?

170
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:51,880
Why do you put your nose
in his business then?

171
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:55,640
I'm just worried about him.

172
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:58,480
Just worry about yourself.

173
00:13:58,560 --> 00:13:59,440
Got it?

174
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,480
Sit down!

175
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:03,680
Sit down!

176
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:04,880
You're so annoying!

177
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,360
Finish your meal.

178
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:25,040
Whether you're rich or poor,

179
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:27,000
whether your record is clean or not,

180
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:29,680
you're still Petch.

181
00:14:30,680 --> 00:14:33,120
My feelings for you stay the same.

182
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:41,920
Hey, Petch.

183
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,760
Go on. Lecture me.

184
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:49,640
But I've made up my mind.

185
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:50,640
Man.

186
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:52,640
I'm not here to lecture you.

187
00:14:53,160 --> 00:14:54,640
I just want to ask you this.

188
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:58,000
Are you really happy with your decision?

189
00:15:04,920 --> 00:15:06,400
I don't care what happens to me.

190
00:15:07,880 --> 00:15:09,760
But I know I did her a favor.

191
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:14,440
You mean,

192
00:15:14,520 --> 00:15:17,760
you're going to quit your job
every time you see her?

193
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:21,480
That's right.

194
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:23,960
If I see her, I'll quit.

195
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:27,560
But if it upsets you,

196
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:30,320
you don't have to quit your job.

197
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:33,280
Got it?

198
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:35,040
Petch.

199
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:37,560
Petch.

200
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:43,160
You'd better think this through.

201
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:46,280
You can run away from everything.

202
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:49,240
But you can't run away

203
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:51,160
from your heart.

204
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:13,320
Doctor.

205
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,080
The patient has heart disease,

206
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:17,600
diabetes, and high blood pressure.

207
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:19,680
How is she at the moment?

208
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:21,040
She's safe.

209
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:24,000
But I would like to observe
her symptoms here for a night.

210
00:16:24,080 --> 00:16:27,720
Relatives must help her
take medication as prescribed

211
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,680
and must not cause her stress.

212
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:33,760
Otherwise, she'll have
a sudden cardiac arrest

213
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:36,640
or a hemorrhagic stroke.

214
00:16:47,400 --> 00:16:48,480
Ake.

215
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:51,240
- Good afternoon, ma'am.
- Hi.

216
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:55,080
You shouldn't have bothered.

217
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:58,720
You've already done enough last night.

218
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:01,400
Thank you so much.

219
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:04,760
Things could have gone worse
if you weren't there.

220
00:17:04,839 --> 00:17:06,520
It's nothing, ma'am.

221
00:17:06,599 --> 00:17:11,119
I want to take care of both of you
like you're my own parents.

222
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:15,119
BOONYAVEJ HOSPITAL

223
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:19,240
Excuse me. I need to take this call.
I'll be right back.

224
00:17:19,319 --> 00:17:20,560
- Ake, stay with Pen.
- All right, sir.

225
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:21,560
All right.

226
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:23,720
Hello?

227
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:26,119
Yes. Have you reviewed your contract?

228
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:31,800
Ma'am.

229
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:35,800
I think we can

230
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:38,160
turn this crisis into an opportunity.

231
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,720
How?

232
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:45,360
Dao is approving paperwork
at the office right now.

233
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:46,640
She'll be here soon.

234
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:52,040
I think you know what move to make
to get Dao to get engaged to me.

235
00:17:55,120 --> 00:17:56,360
Oh, I see.

236
00:17:56,880 --> 00:18:01,040
If I fake my symptoms
as if I'm getting worse,

237
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:03,000
Dao will honor my wish.

238
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:06,080
Good idea. We'll go with that plan.

239
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:07,280
All right, ma'am.

240
00:18:11,360 --> 00:18:12,480
How are you, Mom?

241
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:13,600
Dao.

242
00:18:14,120 --> 00:18:16,360
I came straight from work.
I didn't get you anything.

243
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:17,960
That's okay, sweetheart.

244
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:20,560
Ake brought me a basket full of fruits.

245
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:22,320
I'll peel some for you.

246
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:25,480
- That hurts.
- Mom!

247
00:18:29,080 --> 00:18:31,520
It felt like my heart stopped beating.

248
00:18:31,600 --> 00:18:33,440
I'll call the doctor.

249
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:35,000
No need, sweetheart.

250
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:38,040
Don't call the doctor. Just stay with me.

251
00:18:38,120 --> 00:18:40,080
I'm fine now.

252
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:42,080
Are you sure?

253
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:48,040
Right now, I'm fine.

254
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:51,760
But I'm not sure

255
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:54,600
how much time I've got left.

256
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:56,920
Please don't talk like that.

257
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:59,280
You must live long with me.

258
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:01,520
Ma'am.

259
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:05,400
I'll find the finest doctor to treat you.

260
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:07,440
Don't worry about a thing.

261
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:12,040
I'm not worried about myself.

262
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:14,720
I'm worried about Dao.

263
00:19:15,480 --> 00:19:17,160
When I'm gone,

264
00:19:17,880 --> 00:19:22,760
Dao should have someone
who can take care of and protect her.

265
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:29,800
Ake.

266
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:36,440
Get engaged to Dao.

267
00:19:37,120 --> 00:19:39,440
Can you take care of her on my behalf?

268
00:19:40,840 --> 00:19:41,680
Well…

269
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:47,920
Of course.

270
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:51,920
Mom.

271
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,800
I can take care of myself.

272
00:19:57,040 --> 00:19:58,480
Mom.

273
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:02,320
Dao.

274
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:06,320
Life is short, sweetheart.

275
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:08,440
Just…

276
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:13,080
get engaged to Ake
and make me happy one last time.

277
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:16,800
Please, my baby girl.

278
00:20:18,440 --> 00:20:20,800
Please do it for your mother.

279
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:30,840
All right, Mom.

280
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:32,880
I'll do it for you.

281
00:20:35,840 --> 00:20:37,360
Thank you, my girl.

282
00:20:50,840 --> 00:20:54,160
BANSUAN NAMSUAY APARTMENT

283
00:20:55,280 --> 00:20:57,800
Do you have coins to exchange with me?

284
00:20:58,480 --> 00:21:00,440
That's 100 baht in cash.

285
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:02,200
I don't have that many coins.

286
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:04,920
Here, keep it.

287
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,000
I have 20. You can take 10.

288
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:10,400
You're just going to give it to me?

289
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:11,760
Just keep it.

290
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:15,120
To prove that there are still
kindhearted people in the capital.

291
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:16,400
Thank you, dear.

292
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:19,080
Where are you from?
You're from out of town, aren't you?

293
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:23,040
Do I have "from out of town"
painted on my forehead?

294
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:24,640
Everyone keeps pointing it out.

295
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:26,360
So where?

296
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:27,400
Takhli District.

297
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:29,360
Girl! I'm from Takhli too.

298
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:31,200
We're from the same neck of the woods.

299
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:33,720
- Thank you, dear.
- Don't mention it.

300
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:46,800
<i>I work as a cook</i>
<i>in the same alley as this pub.</i>

301
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:48,960
<i>I heard they need more waitresses.</i>

302
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:50,520
<i>You should ask them for a job.</i>

303
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:53,720
Excuse me.

304
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:55,240
- Yes?
- Where's the manager's office?

305
00:21:55,320 --> 00:21:56,960
It's that way, miss.

306
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:58,880
Thank you.

307
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:14,840
Come on, guys. Chop-chop!

308
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:16,880
Our pub will open tonight.

309
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:19,520
Tonight, not the next lifetime.

310
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:23,120
The tables are still dirty.

311
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:25,960
You guys are giving me a real headache.

312
00:22:26,040 --> 00:22:27,480
Amateur!

313
00:22:27,560 --> 00:22:28,640
Hurry up!

314
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:30,600
Hello, Mr. Manager!

315
00:22:41,720 --> 00:22:42,760
Hello, beautiful.

316
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:45,440
How can I help you?

317
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:48,120
I want to apply for a job.

318
00:22:48,920 --> 00:22:50,600
Please take me in.

319
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:52,280
I won't forget your benevolence.

320
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:55,400
Oh, girl.

321
00:22:56,240 --> 00:22:58,840
Don't lie to me

322
00:22:59,360 --> 00:23:01,440
because girls always lie to me.

323
00:23:02,880 --> 00:23:04,880
You're so adorable.

324
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:08,120
Sai Kaew, from Takhli,
is a woman of her word.

325
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:11,960
Any job, I guarantee that I can do it.

326
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:14,640
Really?

327
00:23:15,240 --> 00:23:17,680
Very well. I require a 500-baht deposit
before you start.

328
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:20,520
After completing a month,

329
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:23,000
you must pay another 1,000.

330
00:23:23,080 --> 00:23:24,760
- How does that sound?
- Seriously?

331
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:28,280
Taking a 1,500 cut?
That's a bit of a rip-off!

332
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:33,080
It's your call, then.
There are plenty of other pubs out there.

333
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:35,600
There will always be someone
who would love to work here anyway.

334
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:38,040
Go. Leave.

335
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:39,720
Joke!

336
00:23:40,240 --> 00:23:41,080
Shit!

337
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:42,640
Mr. Manager!

338
00:23:44,040 --> 00:23:46,480
Good evening, sir.

339
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:49,040
I didn't see you coming at all.

340
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:52,080
So he's not the manager?

341
00:23:52,760 --> 00:23:53,640
You…

342
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:55,920
I'm the manager.

343
00:23:57,040 --> 00:23:57,920
What were you thinking?

344
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:00,840
I was…

345
00:24:03,240 --> 00:24:05,760
Did you try to scam her for money?

346
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:08,360
No, I didn't!

347
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:12,480
I never had such a thought. Here, look.

348
00:24:12,560 --> 00:24:15,160
There are cameras everywhere.

349
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:17,600
I was just joking. That's it.

350
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:21,240
Fine. Get back to work.

351
00:24:21,320 --> 00:24:24,520
One more thing.

352
00:24:25,040 --> 00:24:27,760
Right now, at the pub,

353
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:31,280
we are short-staffed.

354
00:24:31,360 --> 00:24:32,200
Let's hire her.

355
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:34,400
- Okay?
- I know. Get back to work.

356
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:35,880
- Okay.
- Go!

357
00:24:35,960 --> 00:24:37,240
- All right, sir.
- Get off!

358
00:24:37,320 --> 00:24:39,360
You asshole!

359
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:41,280
Okay!

360
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:44,800
So?

361
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:46,880
Do you want to work here?

362
00:24:48,840 --> 00:24:51,920
I used to be a waitress
at a Thai barbecue restaurant.

363
00:24:52,520 --> 00:24:54,800
My beauty drew many customers.

364
00:24:55,320 --> 00:24:57,720
But the owner wanted me
to be his mistress.

365
00:24:57,800 --> 00:24:59,160
I refused, so I ran away to Bangkok.

366
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,720
Please take me in.

367
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:04,760
I'm pretty and good at sweet talk.

368
00:25:04,840 --> 00:25:07,040
I'm hardworking too.

369
00:25:09,360 --> 00:25:12,160
Come on. I'll give you a massage.
It will help you relax.

370
00:25:14,600 --> 00:25:16,200
Sit still, please.

371
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:17,560
Wait. Hold on.

372
00:25:17,640 --> 00:25:18,840
Are you ticklish?

373
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:20,920
It's not like that!

374
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:24,200
I have an upset stomach.
I need to use the restroom.

375
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:29,160
Your minimum wage
will be calculated separately.

376
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:30,760
You can start tomorrow.

377
00:25:31,360 --> 00:25:33,200
You will really take me in?

378
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:34,120
Yes.

379
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:41,360
I got a job!

380
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:07,320
<i>Being single is so much fun, so much fun</i>

381
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:10,360
<i>Let the whole world know</i>

382
00:26:12,040 --> 00:26:15,680
<i>Let them know that loneliness</i>

383
00:26:15,760 --> 00:26:20,800
<i>Loneliness can't kill me</i>

384
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:25,920
- Stop recording.
- What?

385
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:27,280
Stop it.

386
00:26:27,360 --> 00:26:29,200
Why did you stop?

387
00:26:29,280 --> 00:26:30,920
It was going great.

388
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:32,040
But…

389
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:34,480
the dynamic wasn't that good.

390
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:36,360
If we want more views,

391
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:38,120
the dynamic should be better.

392
00:26:40,280 --> 00:26:43,160
<i>Sathu. </i>Please work out this time.

393
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:45,440
From the top. Ready?

394
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:48,560
Petch <i>Oppa</i>!

395
00:26:49,280 --> 00:26:50,960
I bought you a lot of food.

396
00:26:51,560 --> 00:26:53,040
"Petch <i>Oppa</i>."

397
00:26:55,600 --> 00:26:56,440
What?

398
00:26:56,520 --> 00:26:58,640
Why? Do you envy him?

399
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:00,800
- Let me tell you this.
- What?

400
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:03,280
Petch won't lay his eyes on you.

401
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:04,720
Just leave him alone.

402
00:27:05,320 --> 00:27:08,640
Dam, with an attitude like this,
you're better off dead!

403
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:10,160
- I'll beat you up.
- Hey!

404
00:27:10,240 --> 00:27:11,080
What the hell?

405
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:12,440
Sai.

406
00:27:12,520 --> 00:27:14,920
Sai, stop! Sai!

407
00:27:15,960 --> 00:27:17,920
Why did you buy so many things?

408
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:20,400
I got a job as a waitress at a pub.

409
00:27:20,480 --> 00:27:22,240
The pub is so fancy.

410
00:27:25,840 --> 00:27:26,920
- Really?
- Yes.

411
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:30,440
Congratulations.

412
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:32,000
Let's celebrate.

413
00:27:33,280 --> 00:27:35,080
Come on. Get the table ready.

414
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:41,200
We're delighted and excited
for their engagement.

415
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:43,800
There's someone
who's more excited than you.

416
00:27:44,320 --> 00:27:46,000
Look at Ake.

417
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:47,800
He's so excited. He can't even sit still.

418
00:27:48,920 --> 00:27:51,520
Dao hasn't come down yet.

419
00:27:52,040 --> 00:27:53,920
Imagine how excited he'll be
when she comes down here.

420
00:27:56,360 --> 00:27:57,920
I'm very glad.

421
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:01,600
Finally, the day that I've been
waiting for so long has come.

422
00:28:08,200 --> 00:28:09,240
Here she comes.

423
00:28:41,480 --> 00:28:42,440
Hello, sir.

424
00:28:43,600 --> 00:28:44,560
All right.

425
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:47,880
We should start the ceremony now.

426
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:48,800
I agree.

427
00:29:11,760 --> 00:29:14,800
Dao, give him your hand.

428
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:52,760
Dao, sweetheart.
Put the ring on his ring finger too.

429
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:44,680
Dao.

430
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:53,840
We just got engaged today.

431
00:30:55,040 --> 00:30:56,520
You're already throwing the ring away?

432
00:30:57,120 --> 00:30:58,360
If I could,

433
00:30:59,120 --> 00:31:00,840
I wouldn't wear it at all.

434
00:31:00,920 --> 00:31:02,080
Dao.

435
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:06,920
The ring is beautiful.

436
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:10,120
It would look better on a woman

437
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:12,080
who actually loves you.

438
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:17,160
Dao.

439
00:31:18,280 --> 00:31:19,400
Let go of me.

440
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:21,200
Don't do anything stupid.

441
00:31:22,520 --> 00:31:23,760
You know well

442
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:26,320
that I love only you.

443
00:31:26,840 --> 00:31:28,720
But I don't love you at all.

444
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:31,520
You know why I got engaged to you.

445
00:31:34,120 --> 00:31:35,240
And do you know

446
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:37,640
what will happen to your mom

447
00:31:38,600 --> 00:31:40,000
if you take this ring off?

448
00:31:58,720 --> 00:32:01,200
Enjoy playing hard to get
while we're engaged.

449
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:04,000
After the wedding,

450
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:06,080
I own you.

451
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:09,440
Your heart and your body.

452
00:32:12,120 --> 00:32:13,400
Dao, Ake.

453
00:32:14,120 --> 00:32:15,720
Having a sweet moment, I see.

454
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:18,000
Prae.

455
00:32:18,080 --> 00:32:19,800
I was looking for you.

456
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:23,880
Dao, your hands are ice cold.
Are you all right?

457
00:32:24,840 --> 00:32:27,840
I was thirsty, but I'm all right now.
Let's go.

458
00:32:28,560 --> 00:32:31,280
Don't forget to confirm the engagement
party in the group chat, okay?

459
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:33,000
Our friends keep asking about it.

460
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:34,800
Let's go.

461
00:32:51,240 --> 00:32:52,280
- Hey.
- You devil!

462
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:54,200
- What?
- I thought you were a ghost!

463
00:32:54,280 --> 00:32:56,360
I'm human!

464
00:32:56,440 --> 00:32:59,520
I'm an angel in human form.
What are you up to?

465
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:02,040
This devil… What is it, Joke?

466
00:33:02,120 --> 00:33:04,320
Why are you here?

467
00:33:05,480 --> 00:33:07,960
I'm here to see this beautiful face.

468
00:33:08,040 --> 00:33:12,840
My beautiful Sai Kaew
is touching up her face and lips

469
00:33:12,920 --> 00:33:16,120
while others are working their asses off!

470
00:33:16,200 --> 00:33:17,720
That's not my fault.

471
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:19,840
I'm just stating a fact.

472
00:33:20,720 --> 00:33:21,600
Listen.

473
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:27,720
If you don't want the manager to know,

474
00:33:28,920 --> 00:33:31,600
- my silence costs 20 baht.
- Seriously?

475
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:33,840
You're shaking me down for 20 baht?

476
00:33:35,520 --> 00:33:36,560
Come on.

477
00:33:37,600 --> 00:33:40,000
This is 40 baht.

478
00:33:40,080 --> 00:33:42,960
Please stay far, far away from me.

479
00:33:43,040 --> 00:33:44,360
You're stinking up the air.

480
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:45,280
Damn.

481
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:47,880
Thank you, Sai Kaew.

482
00:33:49,040 --> 00:33:49,920
Joke.

483
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:52,440
- Joke.
- Sir?

484
00:33:52,520 --> 00:33:54,000
Has the band arrived yet?

485
00:33:55,040 --> 00:33:56,800
They haven't, sir.

486
00:33:56,880 --> 00:33:58,320
- What?
- Yes.

487
00:33:58,400 --> 00:34:00,000
Why do they have to be late tonight?

488
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:02,880
Tonight is Ake's engagement party.

489
00:34:02,960 --> 00:34:06,000
- Should you call them, sir?
- Damn it.

490
00:34:08,199 --> 00:34:10,719
Hello? We're waiting for you.

491
00:34:11,679 --> 00:34:12,639
What?

492
00:34:12,719 --> 00:34:14,760
You guys missed the flight.
You can't make it?

493
00:34:15,440 --> 00:34:17,000
Tonight is for Ake!

494
00:34:17,080 --> 00:34:18,520
The next flight is at 11:00 p.m.?

495
00:34:18,600 --> 00:34:20,280
Come on!

496
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:22,400
Don't come. Just find some gig over there!

497
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:23,520
That's it.

498
00:34:24,199 --> 00:34:25,040
Damn.

499
00:34:25,560 --> 00:34:27,639
Damn it, man.

500
00:34:27,719 --> 00:34:29,600
I wish I could beat them up!

501
00:34:29,679 --> 00:34:31,960
Right. You're right.

502
00:34:33,159 --> 00:34:35,760
If we can't bring a band tonight,

503
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:37,560
we're the ones getting beaten up.

504
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:42,199
We only have an hour. What should we do?

505
00:34:44,760 --> 00:34:46,560
My brother has a band.

506
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:51,920
The singer is talented
and has a beautiful voice.

507
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:54,400
Plus, his rate is very friendly.

508
00:34:55,400 --> 00:34:58,560
I don't care what his rate is
as long as he sings well.

509
00:34:58,640 --> 00:35:00,920
Trust me. He sings well.

510
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:03,120
If I let you down,
you can step on my face.

511
00:35:07,280 --> 00:35:08,560
Okay. Hire him.

512
00:35:08,640 --> 00:35:10,840
Call him to come here ASAP.

513
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:13,760
Roger that, Mr. Manager.

514
00:35:37,240 --> 00:35:39,360
Good evening, sir, ma'am.

515
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:42,880
Is everything inside all right?

516
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:45,160
Everything is all right. Please, sir.

517
00:35:45,880 --> 00:35:47,360
Let's go.

518
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:56,680
Pull over, sir. Pull over here.

519
00:35:57,200 --> 00:35:58,720
Here we are.

520
00:36:05,440 --> 00:36:07,600
The wind hurt my ears.

521
00:36:08,640 --> 00:36:11,160
It's about time. Let's go.

522
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:14,000
Petch! Dam! This way!

523
00:36:14,080 --> 00:36:15,120
Come on.

524
00:36:17,200 --> 00:36:18,440
Come on.

525
00:36:18,520 --> 00:36:20,280
Come on in.

526
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:32,640
Hey.

527
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:35,520
There you are, Sai Kaew.

528
00:36:37,120 --> 00:36:40,360
He's the singer for the party?

529
00:36:40,440 --> 00:36:42,680
Joke is the head waiter.

530
00:36:42,760 --> 00:36:45,440
They're Petch and Dam.
They're my big brothers.

531
00:36:46,040 --> 00:36:47,440
We'll try our best.

532
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:50,760
That's okay.
I'll take care of both of you.

533
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:54,120
Sai Kaew,
tell Mud that we're about to start.

534
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:57,680
I'll go with you. I want to see the stage.

535
00:37:03,360 --> 00:37:04,840
Young man.

536
00:37:05,600 --> 00:37:06,560
What's with the clothes?

537
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:08,920
You look too poor to be a singer.

538
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:12,240
I came as fast as I could.

539
00:37:12,760 --> 00:37:14,160
I didn't have time to dress properly.

540
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:17,120
Young man, you're not a professional.

541
00:37:17,200 --> 00:37:21,000
Professionals must always be ready.

542
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:23,360
What should I do?

543
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:27,680
Okay. I'll do you a favor.

544
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:31,360
You can rent my suit. Is that okay?

545
00:37:32,080 --> 00:37:33,400
Rent your suit?

546
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:35,960
Right. Rent my suit.

547
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:41,200
Everyone.

548
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:45,160
Let's drink to the most perfect couple.

549
00:37:47,760 --> 00:37:49,240
Cheers.

550
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:52,600
Congratulations to Dao and Ake.

551
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:54,560
Thank you.

552
00:37:55,080 --> 00:37:58,760
I would like to thank all of you.

553
00:37:58,840 --> 00:38:02,160
I wish you all the happiness that we have.

554
00:38:02,680 --> 00:38:03,920
Akekaphol.

555
00:38:04,520 --> 00:38:07,440
We would love to see you two
kiss on the cheek.

556
00:38:07,520 --> 00:38:08,560
Wouldn't we?

557
00:38:09,080 --> 00:38:12,680
- What are you waiting for? Kiss her!
- Kiss him!

558
00:38:12,760 --> 00:38:17,080
- Kiss her!
- Kiss him!

559
00:38:17,920 --> 00:38:19,560
I need to use the restroom.

560
00:38:22,920 --> 00:38:25,360
Dao. Dao, wait up.

561
00:38:25,440 --> 00:38:26,440
Excuse me.

562
00:38:27,160 --> 00:38:28,160
Dao, wait up!

563
00:38:29,080 --> 00:38:33,520
You see, my fiancée…

564
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:34,840
She's a little shy.

565
00:38:43,360 --> 00:38:44,240
Dao.

566
00:38:45,280 --> 00:38:48,000
Are you all right?
You haven't smiled the entire day.

567
00:38:48,680 --> 00:38:51,200
You look upset,
as if you didn't just get engaged.

568
00:38:52,120 --> 00:38:54,880
I'm just exhausted.
There are so many things to take care of.

569
00:38:55,760 --> 00:38:58,880
I'll have to take care
of the opening band too.

570
00:38:58,960 --> 00:39:02,400
You two should have some appetizers.
I'll catch up later.

571
00:39:14,040 --> 00:39:16,680
Here. Choose whichever you like.

572
00:39:16,760 --> 00:39:17,760
Two hundred baht.

573
00:39:19,480 --> 00:39:20,720
Two hundred?

574
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:23,120
What? Do you want a suit or not?

575
00:39:23,200 --> 00:39:24,960
It's okay if you say no.

576
00:39:25,040 --> 00:39:28,560
But brace yourself
for absolute embarrassment.

577
00:39:28,640 --> 00:39:31,920
There are a lot of people in there.

578
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:33,160
So?

579
00:39:34,920 --> 00:39:36,560
These are all fine suits.

580
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:42,440
Fine. But I'll pay you after my gig.

581
00:39:44,400 --> 00:39:46,800
No worries.

582
00:39:47,560 --> 00:39:49,280
Better late than never.

583
00:39:49,360 --> 00:39:51,480
Come on. Take a look.

584
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:54,960
All fine suits here.

585
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:56,400
All Joke's selection.

586
00:39:57,440 --> 00:39:58,680
Fine quality.

587
00:39:59,200 --> 00:40:00,160
Classy.

588
00:40:00,240 --> 00:40:01,080
Petch.

589
00:40:13,400 --> 00:40:14,600
Oh, wow.

590
00:40:15,120 --> 00:40:17,560
It's a full house. What party is it?

591
00:40:18,240 --> 00:40:20,560
The pub owner's engagement party.

592
00:40:21,160 --> 00:40:22,400
Who?

593
00:40:22,480 --> 00:40:23,720
That's all I know.

594
00:40:23,800 --> 00:40:26,040
I just started working here.
I haven't met the owner.

595
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:30,560
Where's the manager?

596
00:40:32,080 --> 00:40:33,320
Excuse me.

597
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:35,040
I'll have one, please.

598
00:40:45,640 --> 00:40:48,360
Do you know him, ma'am?

599
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:50,480
She mistook me for someone else.

600
00:40:53,120 --> 00:40:54,440
How could a poor musician

601
00:40:55,200 --> 00:40:56,880
know a VIP guest?

602
00:40:57,760 --> 00:40:59,520
Yes, that's right.

603
00:41:00,160 --> 00:41:01,240
She doesn't know you.

604
00:41:02,080 --> 00:41:04,840
And she's not just a VIP guest.

605
00:41:05,600 --> 00:41:08,440
Let me introduce her. This is Ms. Natedao.

606
00:41:08,520 --> 00:41:10,280
She is the executive of this pub.

607
00:41:10,880 --> 00:41:15,600
She has the authority to hire you
or even kick you out.

608
00:41:28,280 --> 00:41:29,400
That's Ake.

609
00:41:30,480 --> 00:41:31,880
Why is he here?

610
00:41:38,320 --> 00:41:39,200
Have fun.

611
00:41:43,120 --> 00:41:44,480
Dao and Ake?

612
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:49,160
The engagement party.

613
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:53,480
Ms. Dao and Ake. Petch!

614
00:41:54,080 --> 00:41:55,640
Are you the opening band for tonight?

615
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:57,960
Exactly, ma'am!

616
00:41:58,040 --> 00:42:02,080
Our regular band couldn't make it
because they missed their flight.

617
00:42:02,160 --> 00:42:03,800
Get back to work, Joke.

618
00:42:03,880 --> 00:42:06,560
I've already ordered my men.

619
00:42:06,640 --> 00:42:07,920
I'm available now.

620
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:10,320
- Let me take care of you, ma'am. Because--
- No need.

621
00:42:11,240 --> 00:42:12,280
Just leave.

622
00:42:13,720 --> 00:42:14,760
Well…

623
00:42:15,440 --> 00:42:19,120
I'd better monitor my crew.

624
00:42:19,200 --> 00:42:22,080
So excuse me, ma'am.

625
00:42:22,800 --> 00:42:23,960
Have a good night.

626
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:25,960
Behave.

627
00:42:32,560 --> 00:42:33,520
Where are you going?

628
00:42:35,760 --> 00:42:38,200
Are you going to keep running
from me for the rest of your life?

629
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:40,880
I've told you before.

630
00:42:41,560 --> 00:42:43,560
We don't have to see each other again.

631
00:42:51,080 --> 00:42:51,920
Petch!

632
00:42:52,960 --> 00:42:54,680
This is Ake's and Dao's engagement party.

633
00:43:03,160 --> 00:43:04,640
Did you hear him?

634
00:43:05,600 --> 00:43:06,960
I'm now engaged to Ake.

635
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:10,680
The past doesn't matter to me now.

636
00:43:12,120 --> 00:43:14,520
If you sing well,
I'll let you have more gigs here.

637
00:43:15,120 --> 00:43:19,320
You mean Petch and I
can really play music here?

638
00:43:21,160 --> 00:43:22,120
Yes.

639
00:43:23,600 --> 00:43:26,320
If your band plays well,
I'll hire you as our regular band.

640
00:43:27,400 --> 00:43:29,120
What do you say?

641
00:43:29,200 --> 00:43:31,280
I'm perfectly fine with that.

642
00:43:31,360 --> 00:43:32,560
Petch, get ready.

643
00:43:32,640 --> 00:43:33,880
I'm a man of my word.

644
00:43:37,200 --> 00:43:38,360
You can work here without me, Dam.

645
00:43:38,440 --> 00:43:41,440
Are you crazy? We've come this far.

646
00:43:41,520 --> 00:43:43,600
How could you abandon me like this?

647
00:43:44,120 --> 00:43:45,320
Give me a break, man.

648
00:43:45,400 --> 00:43:46,680
If I force myself to sing,

649
00:43:47,560 --> 00:43:48,640
it won't sound good anyway.

650
00:43:49,680 --> 00:43:51,600
You must sing.

651
00:43:51,680 --> 00:43:52,760
You must do your job.

652
00:43:52,840 --> 00:43:54,320
Let him go.

653
00:43:56,400 --> 00:43:59,560
I have nothing to say
except I'm so disappointed

654
00:44:00,320 --> 00:44:01,760
to see you being so selfish.

655
00:44:18,440 --> 00:44:20,160
Is the piano soundcheck okay?

656
00:44:20,240 --> 00:44:22,040
Good to go, ma'am.

657
00:44:24,400 --> 00:44:25,440
Dao.

658
00:44:26,720 --> 00:44:28,440
I apologize on behalf of Petch.

659
00:44:29,040 --> 00:44:30,600
Don't worry.

660
00:44:32,080 --> 00:44:33,080
Thank you.

661
00:44:34,400 --> 00:44:35,280
Right.

662
00:44:36,600 --> 00:44:39,320
This is my number and Petch's.

663
00:44:39,400 --> 00:44:42,080
You can call us for other gigs.

664
00:44:43,520 --> 00:44:44,960
Of course, there are gigs for you.

665
00:44:45,040 --> 00:44:47,160
But your friend might not accept it.

666
00:44:48,480 --> 00:44:49,360
Forget him.

667
00:44:49,440 --> 00:44:51,760
I'll get ready for the stage.

668
00:44:52,600 --> 00:44:53,760
Piano?

669
00:44:53,840 --> 00:44:54,680
Yes.

670
00:44:55,600 --> 00:44:59,360
Your friend turned down the offer,
so I have to perform the music myself.

671
00:44:59,960 --> 00:45:01,720
I can only play instrumental songs.

672
00:45:01,800 --> 00:45:03,400
I'm not good at singing.

673
00:45:04,360 --> 00:45:06,280
All right. Good luck, then.

674
00:45:11,320 --> 00:45:12,480
Petch, you idiot.

675
00:45:13,000 --> 00:45:15,080
You shouldn't have done that.

676
00:45:18,080 --> 00:45:20,000
Mr. Manager!

677
00:45:20,080 --> 00:45:21,120
- What?
- Oh, no!

678
00:45:21,920 --> 00:45:23,760
I'm sorry! I'll help you clean it up!

679
00:45:23,840 --> 00:45:24,720
Hey!

680
00:45:25,680 --> 00:45:29,480
Disgusting!
Keep your dirty hands away from my shirt.

681
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:30,680
Sir.

682
00:45:31,400 --> 00:45:34,360
Please calm down.
This won't look good for your image.

683
00:45:38,840 --> 00:45:40,360
I forgive you.

684
00:45:41,480 --> 00:45:43,280
Only because it's my engagement day.

685
00:45:44,240 --> 00:45:48,000
Oh, you are Akekaphol, the pub owner.

686
00:45:48,520 --> 00:45:51,240
Of course. Hey, Mud.

687
00:45:52,640 --> 00:45:53,680
Who's this kid?

688
00:45:54,800 --> 00:45:57,600
She's Sai Kaew, our newest waitress.

689
00:45:59,040 --> 00:46:01,480
Is there something wrong, Sai Kaew?

690
00:46:01,560 --> 00:46:02,440
Oh, right.

691
00:46:02,960 --> 00:46:06,400
The band that I brought here,
they're in the dressing room.

692
00:46:06,480 --> 00:46:07,760
Should they start now?

693
00:46:08,440 --> 00:46:11,040
What band?

694
00:46:11,120 --> 00:46:13,640
Our regular band couldn't make it.

695
00:46:13,720 --> 00:46:16,640
Sai Kaew helped me
find a new band for tonight.

696
00:46:18,400 --> 00:46:19,880
Are they cool?

697
00:46:20,600 --> 00:46:22,400
I don't want a lame

698
00:46:23,320 --> 00:46:24,480
and lousy band.

699
00:46:25,760 --> 00:46:30,800
I know, sir. This pub is too prestigious
for commoners like us.

700
00:46:31,760 --> 00:46:33,400
Are you mocking me?

701
00:46:33,480 --> 00:46:35,520
Sir!

702
00:46:35,600 --> 00:46:36,920
Please calm down.

703
00:46:37,000 --> 00:46:38,920
Do you want to do the sound check?

704
00:46:39,440 --> 00:46:41,040
We still have some time left.

705
00:46:43,200 --> 00:46:44,360
Fine.

706
00:46:44,440 --> 00:46:45,880
I want to know

707
00:46:46,600 --> 00:46:50,000
how special the band you brought me is.

708
00:46:53,440 --> 00:46:54,440
This way, sir.

709
00:46:56,720 --> 00:46:57,560
Hey!

710
00:47:03,800 --> 00:47:05,000
Akekaphol.

711
00:47:05,800 --> 00:47:08,920
If you have no money,
you'll be beaten to death.

712
00:47:13,760 --> 00:47:15,480
Hold on.

713
00:47:15,560 --> 00:47:17,120
Where are you going?

714
00:47:19,200 --> 00:47:21,120
Where's my deposit?

715
00:47:23,880 --> 00:47:25,040
- Come on.
- Take it back.

716
00:47:26,960 --> 00:47:28,560
Hey, kid!

717
00:47:29,200 --> 00:47:30,480
What's wrong with you?

718
00:47:31,000 --> 00:47:33,200
You won't get up on the stage?

719
00:47:35,840 --> 00:47:37,200
- He ruined my suit.
- Petch.

720
00:47:38,080 --> 00:47:39,200
Think this through.

721
00:47:39,280 --> 00:47:41,600
I followed Ms. Dao backstage.

722
00:47:41,680 --> 00:47:43,760
She's going to play the piano herself.

723
00:47:43,840 --> 00:47:45,120
What?

724
00:47:45,200 --> 00:47:50,520
She can't find any singer to replace you,
so she'll perform the music herself.

725
00:47:54,600 --> 00:47:55,600
- Mud.
- Sir?

726
00:47:56,120 --> 00:47:57,920
Why is Dao going up on the stage?

727
00:47:58,520 --> 00:48:00,240
This is unscripted.

728
00:48:02,800 --> 00:48:04,920
Come on, man.

729
00:48:05,440 --> 00:48:06,840
We're doomed.

730
00:48:06,920 --> 00:48:07,800
Hear that?

731
00:48:08,320 --> 00:48:10,360
It's only instrumental with no vocals.

732
00:48:10,440 --> 00:48:11,840
How can that entertain people?

733
00:48:58,520 --> 00:49:00,560
I would like to thank all of you

734
00:49:00,640 --> 00:49:02,320
for coming tonight.

735
00:49:03,120 --> 00:49:04,920
The next song

736
00:49:05,840 --> 00:49:07,480
is my most beloved song.

737
00:49:09,000 --> 00:49:10,040
Let's listen to it together.

738
00:49:23,560 --> 00:49:27,560
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

739
00:49:29,400 --> 00:49:33,960
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

740
00:49:35,320 --> 00:49:36,240
<i>For my heart…</i>

741
00:49:36,320 --> 00:49:37,720
Damn it!

742
00:49:38,240 --> 00:49:41,920
Petch and Ms. Dao
performed harmoniously together.

743
00:49:42,720 --> 00:49:45,560
I wonder what Ake thought about it.

744
00:49:45,640 --> 00:49:48,880
Tell Petch and his friends

745
00:49:50,000 --> 00:49:51,400
to see me here.

746
00:49:52,000 --> 00:49:54,880
- Who are you?
- I'm Sai Kaew, Damrong's younger sister.

747
00:49:55,640 --> 00:49:57,160
We'd better go help Petch.

748
00:49:57,240 --> 00:49:58,120
What's going on?

749
00:49:58,720 --> 00:50:00,440
Akekaphol asked to see Petch.

750
00:50:00,520 --> 00:50:01,960
I'm afraid something bad might happen.

751
00:50:02,040 --> 00:50:07,880
NEXT EPISODE

752
00:50:19,400 --> 00:50:24,360
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

753
00:50:25,280 --> 00:50:30,440
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

754
00:50:31,480 --> 00:50:37,440
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

755
00:50:37,520 --> 00:50:42,080
<i>But never reaching you</i>

756
00:50:43,400 --> 00:50:48,320
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

757
00:50:49,520 --> 00:50:54,320
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

758
00:50:56,000 --> 00:51:01,240
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

759
00:51:01,880 --> 00:51:07,280
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

760
00:51:08,880 --> 00:51:12,840
<i>You are out of reach</i>

761
00:51:13,560 --> 00:51:18,840
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

762
00:51:20,520 --> 00:51:24,720
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

763
00:51:25,480 --> 00:51:30,680
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

764
00:51:31,560 --> 00:51:35,720
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

765
00:51:37,520 --> 00:51:41,960
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

766
00:51:43,520 --> 00:51:49,080
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

767
00:51:49,600 --> 00:51:55,240
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

768
00:51:55,320 --> 00:51:56,960
Subtitle translation by: Sarunpon T.
